UNITED STATES of America ex rel. WONG LEON KEN, Appellant, v. Rudolph REIMER, Director of Immigration, Appellee. No. 351. 'Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 29, 1939. James C. Thomas, of New York City, for appellant. John T. Cahill, U. S. Atty., of New York City (David McKibbin, 3d, Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before L. HAND, CHASE, and PATTERSON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed.
